  "prompt": "What are some less fictioned movie everyone must watch?",
  "response": "There are many compelling non-fiction films that cover a wide range of topics, from biographies to documentaries. Here are some noteworthy ones that everyone should consider watching:\n\n1. **The Act of Killing (2012)** - A haunting documentary that explores the Indonesian killings of 1965-66 through the perspective of former death squad leaders.\n\n2. **13th (2016)** - Directed by Ava DuVernay, this documentary examines the intersection of race, justice, and mass incarceration in the United States.\n\n3. **Won't You Be My Neighbor? (2018)** - A touching portrait of Fred Rogers, the beloved host of the television show \"Mister Rogers' Neighborhood,\" and his philosophy of kindness and compassion.\n\n4. **Jiro Dreams of Sushi (2011)** - A documentary about Jiro Ono, a renowned sushi chef, and his relentless pursuit of perfection in his craft.\n\n5. **Blackfish (2013)** - This documentary investigates the controversial captivity of orcas and the consequences of keeping them in marine parks.\n\n6. **Food, Inc. (2008)** - A documentary that looks at the agricultural industry in the United States and the negative impacts of industrial food production.\n\n7. **The Fog of War (2003)** - This film features former U.S. Secretary of Defense Robert S. McNamara reflecting on his experiences and the complexities of war.\n\n8. **Icarus (2017)** - Initially focusing on amateur cyclist Bryan Fogel's attempts to enhance his performance through doping, it soon uncovers a major international sports scandal.\n\n9. **Free Solo (2018)** - Follow rock climber Alex Honnold as he attempts to climb El Capitan in Yosemite National Park without any ropes.\n\n10. **The Social Dilemma (2020)** - A documentary-drama hybrid that explores the dangerous human impact of social networking, featuring tech experts who sound the alarm on their own creations.\n\nThese films are not only informative but also provoke thought and reflection on significant societal issues, historical events, and the human experience.",
